-- Economiesuisse Doubts Capital Control Use, SonntagsZeitung Says
-- B y   D e r m o t   D o h e r t y
-- 2012-06-03T10:48:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-03/economiesuisse-doubts-capital-control-use-sonntagszeitung-says.html
Economiesuisse doubts that the
introduction of  capital controls  to curb the strength of the
Swiss franc would be the “right instrument,”  SonntagsZeitung 
reported, citing Pascal Gentinetta, chairman of the executive
board of the Swiss business group.  The use of negative interest rates in the 1970s was
negative, Gentinetta said in an interview with the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dermot Doherty in Geneva at 
 ddoherty9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
